Field Detail

KEY_VALUE_SEPARATOR

public static final java.lang.String KEY_VALUE_SEPARATOR
The key-value separator in property configurations. This is different from the default (=, :, or white space). It means that when a property is programmatically added, the required escaping with a backslash is done automatically. If values are entered manually, the escaping must still be performed manually
